🛠️ The 2 Fixes You Need
Fix 1: Install the Missing WebSocket Library
Look at the repeated warning in your terminal:

WARNING: No supported WebSocket library detected. Please use "pip install 'uvicorn[standard]'" ...

Uvicorn needs a helper package to read and process WebSockets. Because it's missing, Uvicorn is rejecting the browser's handshake request.

How to fix it:

Shut down your running server in the terminal by pressing Ctrl + C.

Run this command to install the required WebSocket support:

Bash
pip install websockets
(Alternatively, you can run pip install "uvicorn[standard]")

Fix 2: The HTTP 404 Not Found fallback
Look at the line below the warning:

INFO: ... - "GET /ws HTTP/1.1" 404 Not Found

Because Uvicorn doesn't have the WebSocket library installed, it treated your WebSocket request (ws://...) like a normal website link (http://...). Since there is no standard web page at /ws, it threw a 404 Not Found error.

🚀 Let's Bring It All Together
Once you install the library, restart everything in this exact order:

Start your backend server again:

Bash
uvicorn app:app --reload
Go back to your browser window at http://127.0.0.1:8000/.

Press Ctrl + F5 (or Cmd + Shift + R on Mac) to force a hard refresh.

The red connection banner should disappear instantly, replaced by your green "🟢 Secure Real-Time Link Connected" badge, and your toggles, panic button, and random data generator will start working seamlessly!



